{"id":"a8e4f13aeecc45a3b8fab3ecfd9ddb5d70fb772b","axis":"silent","repo":"axios/axios","sha":"a8e4f13aeecc45a3b8fab3ecfd9ddb5d70fb772b","parsed":{"files":[{"path":"PRE_RELEASE_CHANGELOG.md","lines":["@@ -9,3 +9,8 @@"," ## Bug Fixes"," "," - **Types:** Add the missing readonly `name: 'CanceledError'` declaration to CommonJS `CanceledError` typings to match the ESM declarations. (**#10922**)","+- **Config Merge:** Added `transitional.validateStatusUndefinedResolves` (default `true`) so applications can opt into treating explicit `validateStatus: undefined` like an omitted option by setting it to `false`. `validateStatus: null` still accepts every response status. (**#10899**, closes **#6688**)","+","+## Release Tracking","+","+- ESM/CJS typings are updated for `transitional.validateStatusUndefinedResolves`; README/docs updates are tracked in `PRE_RELEASE_DOCS.md` for release preparation."],"additions":5,"deletions":0,"truncated":false},{"path":"PRE_RELEASE_DOCS.md","lines":["@@ -37,3 +37,23 @@ axios.get('https://api.example.com/users', {"," ```"," "," - **Notes:** Add a security page row linking to the request-config section and add a `sensitiveHeaders` request-config entry marked Node.js only.","+","+### validateStatus undefined transitional option","+","+- **Change:** Document `transitional.validateStatusUndefinedResolves` for the `validateStatus: undefined` merge behavior.","+- **Source:** `PRE_RELEASE_CHANGELOG.md` Bug Fixes, #10899, closes #6688.","+- **Status:** Pending.","+- **Docs targets:** README request config section; `docs/pages/advanced/request-config.md` `validateStatus` section and request config example; translated request-config docs after English docs are finalized.","+- **Required content:** Explain that `validateStatus: undefined` keeps legacy behavior by default and resolves every response status because `transitional.validateStatusUndefinedResolves` defaults to `true`. Explain that setting `transitional.validateStatusUndefinedResolves` to `false`